I'm giving this place five stars for being the best service one can get in this area. It's practically a food desert on this side of Atlanta. That makes this sándwich shop much more valuable. The shop is small, orderly, and Asian run. They serve mostly fried southern foods and Chinese dishes. The owners and the family that owns the establishment are awesome people. I personally like to chat with the cashier or cook whenever I have extra time.  The place is very busy because of its status as one of the few restaurants in the are. But it is also quick. They make every order on demand as well.  yes I recommend this place. Not just because the fried foods are good but because they are an oasis in a food desert.
